Jackie Bavaro says good product sense looks like : 

- Deeply understand the goals of a product, both for the business and the customer
- How the product is serving those goals
- Finding opportunities to better serve goals

[https://jackiebo.medium.com/five-exercises-to-practice-product-sense-57b9104ef8da](https://jackiebo.medium.com/five-exercises-to-practice-product-sense-57b9104ef8da)

[https://medium.com/we-are-yammer/product-teardowns-at-yammer-e2c4d5f0e2ff](https://medium.com/we-are-yammer/product-teardowns-at-yammer-e2c4d5f0e2ff)

**Practice - Goals**

- Write down all the goals you can think of the product â†’ Consider who built the product, who purchases and who uses the product, what motivated them to buy or use it?, Is this a luxury good or mass marked good? Is it for entertainment or productivity? Look at Pr & Marketing for the product

