### Product Sense â†’ Lenny

[https://www.lennysnewsletter.com/p/product-sense?s=r](https://www.lennysnewsletter.com/p/product-sense?s=r)

Craft products or make changes to existing products that have the intended impact on their users.

Product Sense relies on

- Empathy â†’ to discover meaningful needs
- Creativity â†’ come up with effective solutions to address needs

**Building Empathy**

- Observe people interacting with products
    - What do you think is the purpose of the product is?  Who it is for?
    - How was the workflow? Onboarding? Repeat usage?
    - How does it make usersâ€™s feel
- Deconstruct everyday products
    - [https://medium.com/the-year-of-the-looking-glass/how-to-do-a-product-critique-98b657050638#.v5o81mocz](https://medium.com/the-year-of-the-looking-glass/how-to-do-a-product-critique-98b657050638#.v5o81mocz)
    - Delight moments

**Building Creativity**

- Learn from great product thinkers
    - Be in a good company of product thinkers. Attend as many product reviews. Or look for external product thinkers
        - What prompted to build your product?
        - What were the key decision points along the way?
        - What alternative approaches did you consider?
        - What were the surprising insights or results?
        - What principle or frameworks helped you navigate the ambiguity?
    - Understand the problem, why that problem exists, and framing them in a way the team understand the constraints
- Be curious about changes in technology and your domain
    - Platform shifts that are happening in your domain
    - Developer conferences of Google, Apple, Meta, Amazong, Ben Thomson

**How do you know you are getting better at product sense?**

- Notice subtle things about product and people
- Anticipate non-obvious user problems when you look at product experience
- Contribute more unique insights to the team
- Be right more often
- Receive comments from team that they are impressed with a detail you noticed

